title: Mia the Beagle has a bad run at the Westminster Dog Show
text:
Taking a timeout, stopping for a sniff and a scratch won't land you best in show but it certainly provided the best laughs from one Beagle at the 2017 Westminster Dog Show.
Mia the Beagle starts out well in her run at the New York show, overcoming her hurdles with ease but she soon falls a bit short in her competition as she becomes distracted by her surroundings.
After clearing three obstacles he starts sniffing the ground around her as an announcer jokingly says: 'Don't be a beagle, don't be a beagle, come on.'
Scroll down for video
Mia the Beagle fell a bit short during her competition at the 2017 Westminster Dog Show, to hilarious results
Another hurdle - walking up and down a steep path - proves a bit much for her as she stops and turns away from it briefly
At one point Mia stops for a sniff rather than taking on a complex maneuvering obstacle
A video from Fox Sports shows she refocuses but this is comically short-lived as, rather than taking on a complex maneuvering obstacle, she stops to sniff her belly.
Mia then proceeds to knock a bar down at the show in Madison Square Garden In New York City.
And when faced with another hurdle - walking up and down a steep path - she stops and turns away from it briefly.
She started out all well and good, overcoming her hurdles with ease. But after clearing three obstacles, she became a little distracted
Mia unfortunately knocked a bar down at one point but for the most part cleared the rest of her obstacles
Mia tackled this obstacle after having a short time-out for a quick sniff
At the end of her run, the announcer says: 'That was a delightfully entertaining run.'
The dog show sees more than 2,800 dogs compete on February 11, 13 and 14.
Competitions include breed judging, agility and obedience.
